OL,6,FHe said: "He put his face against the
OL,7,Fglass and appeared to lick the knife.
OL,8,FIt was quite bizarre and horrible.
OL,10,F"He tried to stab the doors again to
OL,11,Fbreak the second layer. There was no
OL,12,Fdoubt if he got inside the station, he
OL,13,Fwould have stabbed me or one of the
OL,14,Fofficers with the knife he had.
OL,16,F"The concern was about my colleagues.
OL,17,FMy main concern was him getting out of
OL,18,Fthat compound ... and members of the
OL,19,Fpublic he could easily get to."
